  "local_port": 54868,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I add more than one WordPress site in Godaddy's Deluxe hosting plan?",
  "response": "To host more than one WordPress site on GoDaddy\u2019s Deluxe hosting plan, you need to follow these steps. Keep in mind that GoDaddy\u2019s Deluxe hosting plan supports multiple websites, so you can create and manage several WordPress sites. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Add a Domain for the New WordPress Site:**\n   - Log in to your GoDaddy account.\n   - Go to 'My Products' and find the hosting plan.\n   - Click 'Manage' to access your hosting dashboard.\n   - Under 'Web Hosting', find your Deluxe hosting plan and click 'Manage.'\n   - In your cPanel account, locate the 'Domains' section and click on 'Addon Domains.'\n   - Enter the new domain name you want to add and fill out the required details.\n   - Click 'Add Domain.'\n\n2. **Create a New Database:**\n   - Go back to the cPanel home, and in the 'Databases' section, click on 'MySQL\u00ae Databases.'\n   - Create a new database for your new WordPress site.\n   - Create a new MySQL user and assign it to this new database with all privileges.\n\n3. **Install WordPress:**\n   - In the cPanel, find the 'Web Applications' or 'Software' section.\n   - Click on 'WordPress' to start the installation process.\n   - Choose the new domain from the dropdown menu during the installation process to ensure WordPress is installed on the correct site.\n   - Enter the necessary details like site name, admin username, and password, then complete the installation.\n\n4. **Configure Your WordPress Site:**\n   - Once WordPress is installed, you can access your new site by going to `http://yournewdomain.com/wp-admin`.\n   - Log in with the admin credentials you set up during the installation.\n   - You can now customize your site, install themes, and plugins according to your needs.\n\n5. **Manage Files and Content:**\n   - Use the File Manager or an FTP client to upload themes or plugins directly if needed.\n   - Ensure each website\u2019s files are kept in separate directories under the `public_html` folder or equivalent in your hosting account.\n\n6. **Set Up DNS Records:**\n   - If your domain's DNS is managed elsewhere, ensure you point the domain\u2019s A record to GoDaddy\u2019s server IP where your hosting is located.\n\nAfter completing these steps, your new WordPress site should be live and operational under the same hosting plan. Remember that your hosting plan's resources, such as storage and bandwidth, will be shared among all the sites you have set up.",
